      public <T> void buyIngredient​(T object, double amount)
      As the buy operation for ingredients happens in the warehouse, we put this method in here. It buys the desired amount of the desired object.
      Type Parameters:

    • shipIngredient

      public <T> T shipIngredient​(T object, double amount)
      As the shipping of the ingredients happens in the warehouse, we put this method in here. It removes the ingredients from the storage tanks in the desired amount or the container capacity.
      Type Parameters:
      T - A type parameter.
      Parameters:
      object - An object that is used as a type pointer.
      amount - The desired amount of ingredient to be shipped.
      Returns:
      The removed object.
